<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<section xml:id="sec_dot_prod_summ">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        The dot product of vectors <m>\vu = [u_1 \ u_2 \  \cdots  \ u_n ]^{\tr}</m> and
        <m>\vv = [ v_1 \ v_2 \ \cdots \ v_n ]^{\tr}</m> in <m>\R^n</m> is the scalar
        <me>
          \vu \cdot \vv = u_1v_1 + u_2v_2 + \cdots + u_nv_n = \displaystyle \sum_{i=1}^n u_iv_i
        </me>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The angle <m>\theta</m> between two nonzero vectors <m>\vu</m> and <m>\vv</m> in <m>\R^n</m> satisfies the equation
        <me>
          \cos(\theta) = \frac{\vu \cdot \vv}{||\vu|| \ ||\vv||}
        </me>
        and <m>0\leq \theta \leq 180</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Two vectors <m>\vu</m> and <m>\vv</m> are orthogonal if <m>\vu \cdot \vv = 0</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The length, or norm,
        of the vector <m>\vu</m> can be found as <m>\ds || \vu || = \sqrt{\vu \cdot \vu}</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The distance between the vectors <m>\vu</m> and <m>\vv</m> in <m>\R^n</m> is <m>||\vu - \vv ||</m>,
        which is the length of the difference <m>\vu - \vv</m>.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Let <m>\vu</m> and <m>\vv</m> be vectors in <m>\R^n</m>.
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              The orthogonal projection of <m>\vu</m> onto <m>\vv</m> is the vector
              <me>
                \proj_{\vv} \vu = \frac{\vu \cdot \vv}{||\vv||^2} \vv
              </me>.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              The projection of <m>\vu</m> perpendicular to <m>\vv</m> is the vector
              <me>
                \proj_{\perp \vv} \vu = \vu - \proj_{\vv} \vu
              </me>.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        The orthogonal complement of the subspace <m>W</m> of <m>\R^n</m> is the set
        <me>
          W^{\perp} = \{\vx \in \R^n : \vx \cdot \vw = 0 \text{ for all }  \vw \in W\}
        </me>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>